Hi, jokebookservice1 here, a developer of the isOnline extension. Somebody asked for help with a maths problem, so here you go! :) <div class="br"></div>
  <span class="s"></span> = <span class="d"></span> ÷ <span class="t"></span>
  <div class="info">
    Each minute, <span class="m"></span> travels a certain distance more than <span class="l"></span>. 
  </div>
  <div class="info">
    Let's work out what this distance is.
  </div>
  <span class="l"></span><sub><span class="t"></span></sub>
  -
  <span class="m"></span><sub><span class="t"></span></sub>
  = <input maxlength="1" onkeyup="check1();" class="check1">
  - <input maxlength="1" onkeyup="check1();" class="check1"> = <input maxlength="1" onkeyup="check1();" class="check1"> mins.
  <div class="info unlock1">The problem states that <div class="br"></div>
    
    <span class="m"></span><sub><span class="s"></span></sub>
    -<span class="l"></span><sub><span class="s"></span></sub> = <input class="digTWO" value="10" disabled> mph
    = <input class="digTWO" value="10" disabled> ÷ <input maxlength="2" class="digTWO check2" onkeyup="check2();"> = <sup><input maxlength="1" class="check2" onkeyup="check2();"></sup>/<sub><input maxlength="1" class="check2"onkeyup="check2();"></sub> mi per min
    </div>
    
  <div class="info unlock2">
    Note that if <span class="m"></span> travels <div class="br"> ⅙ × 5 miles</div> more than <span class="l"></span> after 5 minutes, and they finish the race, then in the extra minute, <span class="l"></span> has to make that distance to finish the race. So in 1 minute, <span class="l"></span> travels <div class="br">⅙ × 5 = <sup><input maxlength="1" class="check3" onkeyup="check3();"></sup>/<sub><input maxlength="1" class="check3" onkeyup="check3();"></sub> miles</div>
  </div>
  <div class="info unlock3">
    Finally, we need to convert the units back to mph. <div class="br">
    ⅚ × <input maxlength="2" class="digTWO check4" onkeyup="check4();"> = <sup><input maxlength="3" class="digTHREE check4" onkeyup="check4();"></sup>/<sub><input value="6" disabled></sub> = <input maxlength="2" class="digTWO check4" onkeyup="check4();">mph
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="info unlock4">
    The problem has been solved, but if you want to know how far they travelled, you can take the following rearrangement of the formula at the top of the page <div class="br"><span class="d"></span> = <span class="s"></span> × <span class="t"></span></div> If you plug in the values for <span class="l"></span>, <div class="br"><span class="d"></span> = <input disabled value="50" class="digTWO"> × <input disabled value="0.1" class="digTHREE"> = <input disabled value="5"> miles.</div> So there you go, thanks for sticking along, THE END! :)
  </div>
